Bhumi Pednekar, Ishaan Khatter to star in series 'The Royals'; Zeenat Aman to appear in special role

PTI / Aug 14, 2024, 12:09 (IST)

"When an entitled Prince Charming meets a startup whiz, it's inevitable that they will bump heads! Will their ambitions collide, two worlds clash, or even spark a surprising romance?" read the official description of the show. "The Royals" will also feature Sakshi Tanwar, Nora Fatehi, Dino Morea, Milind Soman, Chunky Panday, Vihaan Samat, Kavya Trehan, Sumukhi Suresh, Udit Arora, Lisa Mishra and Luke Kenny.

Manish Harishankar's allegations against Digangana Suryavanshi are false, claims Police investigation

etimes.in / Aug 04, 2024, 15:12 (IST)

The Mumbai Police have found producer Manish Harishankar's allegations against actress Digangana Suryavanshi to be false. Harishankar accused Suryavanshi of fabricating a business deal involving Akshay Kumar with regards to his show Showstopper . Following the investigation, Suryavanshi's team expressed gratitude for the fair inquiry and announced a defamation case against Harishankar.

Abhay Deol makes shocking statement about masculinity and his sexuality, says, 'I've had all kinds of experiences'

etimes.in / Jul 25, 2024, 10:40 (IST)

In a recent interview, Abhay Deol has said that people put people into a box for their convenience but he wouldn't like to define himself or his sexuality by the western terms as he's had all kinds of experiences. He also says that all of us are 'they, them'.

Zeenat Aman talks about being typecast in commercial films: 'I was just bowing out of the public eye'

etimes.in / Jul 15, 2024, 20:41 (IST)

Zeenat Aman is known for sharing insightful reflections on her Instagram, often delving into her career, films, and life experiences. Recently, she posted a vintage interview clip from the 1980s with BBC Asian Network, discussing her journey in Hindi cinema. Zeenat candidly revealed her initial struggle with being typecast in glamorous roles, expressing a desire for more substantial characters. In the minute-long excerpt, Zeenat lamented the limited opportunities for female actors in mainstream Bollywood, emphasizing how easy it is to get pigeonholed into specific roles. Despite gaining fame with films like "Hare Rama Hare Krishna," she actively pursued more diverse roles in movies such as "Bandhan Kachche Dhaago Ka," "Insaaf Ka Taraazu," and "Satyam Shivam Sundaram." Reflecting on the interview, Zeenat humorously acknowledged how she viewed herself as mature back then, contrasting it with her current perspective on her youthful naivety. She encouraged her followers to cherish both the highs and lows in life, as shown through her evolving career and personal journey.

When Zeenat Aman shared a gorgeous throwback pic with Rekha

etimes.in / Jul 08, 2024, 17:28 (IST)

In the caption, Zeenat waxed nostalgic about their unbreakable bond, writing: "Years would go by without us exchanging a word, then we'd bump into each other on a flight or at the nursery and spend a few hours sharing uninhibited life updates. Anyone else have a friend like that?" Though Zeenat did not explicitly name Rekha, her fans were quick to identify the other actress in the photo.
